bio.experienceSummary: Hello, I'm Kerri-Ann. I have a passion for working with children. I am currently a Part-Time Graduate student at Montclair State, majoring in Clinical Psychology with a concentration in child and adolescent studies. I've previously worked as an early educator at Kinder-care. I've also worked as a Behavioral Assistant, Youth Mentor, and Youth Counselor with children ages 5-17. Additionally, I currently work with different families on care. com as an ad-hoc sitter. I love what I do and will continue to provide care to children while I pursue my degree. My goal is to gain as much experiences as possible, build relationships with families, and pay my way through graduate school. I'm CPR, AED, and first-aid certified. I'm patient, reliable, caring, and supportive. Moreover, safety, wellness, and education is what I value most. Your child/children will be in great hands. I look forward to working with you. Thank you.

description.originalText: Kerri-Ann was great! She showed up on time and was great with my 8 month old. She was very thorough when learning about the schedule and responds quickly. We will definitely hire Kerri again!

bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as being honest, kind and overall positive person. I am available to help you with your kids, household needs and errands etc. 

In my spare time, I like to cook, clean, watch movies, go for long walks and enjoy spending time with family and friends.

One thing you should know about me is reliable, organized and trustworthy. I have 7 nieces and nephews that all range in ages that I am extremely close with.

My skills include patience, compassion and adaptability with any situation.

Hi, I am a mother to 4, I have provided my childcare services to many families for the past 20+yrs, I enjoy being around children and helping others whenever needed, I'm very caring, responsible and hands on, I fully respect every parent wishes. I have lots of energy to keep up with the little ones, I enjoy arts and crafts, taking them to activities and just having fun. I have taken care of children of all ages ranging from 3 months and on for other families, I am also very punctual and ready to take on whatever the day has in store for me. Looking forward to meeting more wonderful families and children. ( note: I HAVE ALLERGIES TO CATS )

description.originalText: Maria is super proactive and hands on. She’s really great with our baby, you can tell she genuinely loves being a mom and adores babies. She’s very attentive to his needs, great with playing with him and reading books to him, and she maintains a safe space for him. And she’s very supportive in all aspects- keeping his playroom tidy, bottle cleanup, daycare bag prep, etc. I strongly recommend her.

bio.experienceSummary: I worked with families with children ages 0-10 years of age. I do mostly all household chores as a live-in nanny, taking care of them in the absence of both parents during the day in a daily basis a few years ago. I did preparing meals, cooking, laundry, cleaning, giving the kids a bath, running errands, driving kids to and from school, drive them to their after school programs and helping them with their homework as much I can. I also travel with the family from time to time locally during school breaks.

description.originalText: Enalyn was amazing with our baby and we highly recommend her. She is so nice and arrived early. She is very hard working. We are looking forward to working with her more!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello. My name is Kiara, 25 years old, I'm Dominican, I have some years of experience with kids. I can help with Travel and Errands and many more.. and I have an open and flexible available time to work, even on weekends in case that is necessary.. love children so much. I like to make sure when I'm around children that they have a smile on their face. I have been taking care of kids since I was in junior high school. hit me up!!

I'd describe my personality as loving, caring & respectfully 

I like working with kids because I enjoy helping, taking care and playing with them.

I'm looking for a job that I can enjoy working with kids 

I started working with kids when I was 16

In my spare time, I like to read and play

One thing you should know about me is I love kids 

My skills include CPR & first aid certified and school bus attendant certified. Also I worked in a day with kids

My name is Deanna, I'm 23 and I've been caring for children for a long time (10+yrs) ages range from newborns to teens. My experiences include being the oldest of 7 children. I'm a very patient person, I love kids. I'd like to think I have a very nice personality, easy to talk to, get along with, and I take pride in what I do. I am at your digression so whatever you like I'd accommodate to what your household needs. I have my own vehicle as well. I also have experience taking in-class CNA courses and am first aid and CPR certified. Also available to care in my home if comfortable!

description.displayText: Deanna is warm and friendly.  She's amazing with children. Playful yet has boundaries. (Which was important to us) She's the oldest of 6 children and it shows. You can tell she was used to looking after multiple kids plus helping her mom out. My daughter was 4 and my twins were 2 at the time. Safety was my first concern and she had a great handle on them from day one. She would take them to the park, make meals and clean up after everything without having to be asked. She was a absolute dream to have in our family.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello, my name is Gianna, I am 23 years old and I am a college student. Ever since I was younger I've always enjoyed helping people. I have experience watching over children and helping with their needs. In the summer of 2017, I was given a chance to work around children and since then I've spent my summers as a counselor, teacher, and assistant working with different age groups in various environments such as camps and daycares. I have over 7 years of experience. I often travel through the boroughs to try new restaurants, visit new places or go to dance classes so I'm open to babysitting anywhere! I like to spend my free time reading, dancing, cooking, doing yoga and trying new hobbies such as roller skating. I would describe myself as being kind, creative, respectful and adventurous. I'm open to working late and I'm great with pets. I'm looking forward to being an addition to your family and creating a safe place and comfortable atmosphere for your children to thrive in.

description.displayText: Gianna and I worked together at a day care and she's shown understanding, patience and empathy for children. You can tell that she has passion for her job,  and that she puts the kids she takes care of first especially when it comes to their safety, as well as their development in manners, boundaries, as well as other areas like speech.

bio.experienceSummary: I am a NJ certified teacher and I am currently employed in a public school. I have over 20 years experience of teaching and caring for children of all ages and abilities. Your child(ren) will be in great hands with me while having fun but most importantly .... safe! I am available on select week nights, the weekends while you run errands, date nights/overnights. I am available in the summer to entertain your children and have a fun summer experience full of outdoor play and exploration. I can instruct educational lessons, engage in physical activities and games indoors/outdoors, do arts/crafts, Science, help with pick up/drop off, you name it! I am dependable, structured, outgoing and trustworthy. Looking forward to helping your family with your little gems!

description.displayText: She is creative, caring. Thinks outside of the box.  She doesn't sit around but loves to be active with kids.  Very dependable. Great personality and will keep kids on schedule and follow parent directions.

bio.experienceSummary:
I am a reliable babysitter

I'd describe my personality as caring reliable and kind

I like working with kids because I have many cousins, and 3 nephews that I basically raised. please contact for further information.

In my child care experience, I prioritize creating a safe, fun, and nurturing environment for kids. I've handled tasks like meal preparation, bedtime routines, and homework supervision while keeping things engaging with creative activities tailored to different age groups. Families appreciate my calm and patient approach, especially when things get stressful, as well as my reliability and adaptability to different schedules and routines. One memorable experience I had was helping a shy child open up and build confidence by consistently being supportive and encouraging, which strengthened our bond over time.
